reviews.text:
This is a nicely sweetened strawberry shortcake type flavor. Reminds me a lot of the shortcakes we used to sell at my old job. Layered yellow cake and fresh cut strawberries with a nice dollop of whipped cream in between with a little more on top for good measure. For me being so burnt out on strawberry, there is a good balance of different strawberry flavors in this that gives me a nice fresh cut berry with a touch of some sweet syrup along with it. Works well in this mix and holds up well to the heavier cake/swirl flavors. In all this is a very good rendition of a light and tasty dessert. Goes great after a meal or just about any other time you're craving some sweets or strawberries. I also think this base could fairly easily be remixed with another fruit. Maybe some FA Forest Fruit or the Blueberry Trinity. &#xD;
&#xD;
Note: I did not mix this myself, I was sent a sample of the recipe by it's creator. Just wanted to mention that. But I like it enough that I'll order the missing flavors so I can mix some more up for myself.
